@startuml mesmerize-smart-3legged-oauth-athena-detailed
title Mesmerize — High-Fidelity SMART on FHIR Launch\n3-Legged OAuth 2.0 / Authorization Code Grant from Athenahealth\nMVP: EHR launch only · EHR SSO · No Mesmerize login · ADR-005 / ADR-002

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 280
skinparam wrapWidth 200
skinparam ParticipantPadding 8
skinparam BoxPadding 8
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF8E7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #C4A35A

actor "Clinician\n(or Nurse / MA)" as User #E8F4E8

box "Athenahealth (EHR)" #F5F5F5
  participant "Athena UI\nHyperspace / chart" as UI
  participant "SMART Launch\nBroker" as LaunchBroker
  participant "OAuth 2.0 /\nOIDC Auth Server" as AS
  participant "FHIR R4\nResource Server" as FHIR
end box

box "Mesmerize SMART App (browser only)" #E3F2FD
  participant "Launch page\n/launch" as Launch
  participant "fhirclient.js\n(SMART client)" as FC
  participant "Callback page\n/callback" as CB
  participant "SMART App UI\n(React 19)" as App
end box

box "Mesmerize Cloud (zero PHI)" #FFF3E0
  participant "SMART App Host\n(static / CloudFront)" as Host
  participant "Platform API\nsession-service etc." as API
  database "Postgres\n(de-identified)" as DB
end box

== A. Preconditions (registration & hosting) ==

note over Host, AS
  **Registered SMART confidential client (architecture)**
  • client_id: **mesmerize-content-evidence**
  • client_name: Mesmerize Patient Education & Billing Evidence
  • launch_url: https://smart.mesmerize.com/launch
  • redirect_uri: https://smart.mesmerize.com/callback
  • grant_types: **authorization_code** (3-legged only for clinician MVP)
  • token_endpoint_auth_method: **private_key_jwt**
  • response_types: code
  • MVP scopes:
    launch/encounter
    patient/Patient.read
    patient/Condition.read
    patient/Encounter.read
    patient/DocumentReference.write
  • Hosting: HTTPS, CORS for EHR origins, iframe-friendly
    (no X-Frame-Options deny for Athena)
  • **Not used for SMART app:** Auth0 / Mesmerize password login
  • **Not MVP:** standalone launch, 2-legged client_credentials,
    imaging scopes (ADR-009)
end note

== B. EHR launch from active chart / encounter ==

User -> UI : Open patient chart + encounter\n(active clinical context)
User -> UI : Click **Mesmerize** (SMART app)
UI -> LaunchBroker : Request EHR launch\nwith current patient + encounter
LaunchBroker -> Host : HTTP(S) navigate iframe to launch_url\n**?iss=<FHIR base URL>&launch=<opaque launch token>**
Host -> Launch : Serve /launch (SPA shell)

note right of Launch
  **Why 3-legged?**
  Provider is already in an Athena encounter.
  App must obtain **authenticated provider** identity
  AND **patient/encounter** launch context.
  2-legged client_credentials cannot do that.
end note

== C. SMART discovery ==

Launch -> FC : EHR launch bootstrap\n(iss, launch)
FC -> FHIR : GET {iss}/.well-known/smart-configuration\n(or metadata / CapabilityStatement as required)
FHIR --> FC : authorization_endpoint\ntoken_endpoint\ncapabilities (launch-ehr, authorize-post, …)\nscopes_supported, code_challenge_methods_supported

note over FC
  fhirclient.js discovers AuthZ + token endpoints
  for this Athena sandbox / production FHIR base.
end note

== D. Authorization Code Grant (leg 1–2: user agent + AuthZ) ==

FC -> FC : Create **state** (CSRF)\nOptional **PKCE** code_verifier/challenge\nif required by Athena tenant config
FC -> AS : **HTTP 302 / authorize**\nresponse_type=**code**\nclient_id=mesmerize-content-evidence\nredirect_uri=https://smart.mesmerize.com/callback\nscope=launch/encounter\n  patient/Patient.read\n  patient/Condition.read\n  patient/Encounter.read\n  patient/DocumentReference.write\naud={iss FHIR base}\nlaunch={launch token}\nstate={state}\n[code_challenge / method if PKCE]

AS -> UI : Reuse existing **Athena EHR SSO session**\n(no Mesmerize credentials prompted)
AS -> AS : Bind authorization code to:\n• authenticated practitioner\n• launch context (patient, encounter)\n• approved scopes\n• client_id + redirect_uri

alt User / org already authorized app
  AS -> CB : **302 redirect**\nhttps://smart.mesmerize.com/callback\n?code={authorization_code}&state={state}
else First-time authorize / consent (if Athena requires)
  AS -> User : Consent / enable app (org policy)
  User -> AS : Approve
  AS -> CB : 302 redirect with code + state
end

CB -> FC : Hand off callback query params
FC -> FC : Validate **state** matches\n(reject if mismatch)

== E. Token exchange (leg 3: SMART app ↔ token endpoint) ==

FC -> AS : **POST token_endpoint**\ngrant_type=**authorization_code**\ncode={authorization_code}\nredirect_uri=https://smart.mesmerize.com/callback\nclient_id=mesmerize-content-evidence\n**client_assertion_type**=\n  urn:ietf:params:oauth:client-assertion-type:jwt-bearer\n**client_assertion**= signed JWT (**private_key_jwt**)\n[code_verifier if PKCE]

note over FC, AS
  Confidential client authenticates with **private_key_jwt**
  (architecture). Private key never leaves Mesmerize control;
  assertion proves client identity at token endpoint.
end note

AS -> AS : Verify code (one-time), client assertion,\nredirect_uri, PKCE (if used), launch binding
AS --> FC : **200 Token response**\naccess_token (EHR FHIR Bearer)\ntoken_type=Bearer\nexpires_in\nscope=(granted)\nid_token (if OIDC claims present)\nrefresh_token (if issued by Athena)\n**patient**={FHIR Patient id}\n**encounter**={FHIR Encounter id}\n[fhirUser / need_patient_banner / …]

FC -> App : SMART session ready **in browser memory only**

note over App #FFCDD2
  **HARD INVARIANT (ADR-002)**
  EHR **access_token**, Patient id, Encounter id, name/MRN
  **MUST NOT** be sent to Mesmerize Platform API, logs, or SQS.
  Token lifetime governed by Athena; app clears on expiry/logout.
end note

== F. Browser-side FHIR reads (EHR access_token) ==

App -> FHIR : GET /Patient/{patient}\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
FHIR --> App : Patient (display name for UI header only)

App -> FHIR : GET /Condition?patient={patient}\n&clinical-status=active\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
FHIR --> App : Condition[] → extract **ICD-10** codes

App -> FHIR : GET /Encounter/{encounter}\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
FHIR --> App : Encounter status / context\n(for chart linkage at writeback time)

note over App
  Acceptance (UC1): recommendations render for the
  **correct** patient/encounter **without** manual re-selection.
end note

== G. Mesmerize Platform session (separate credential) ==

App -> API : **POST /api/sessions**\n{\n  tenantId / organizationId,\n  deviceGroupId,\n  conditions: [ICD-10…],\n  …\n}\nAuthorization: Mesmerize session bootstrap\n(**not** EHR Bearer token)

API -> DB : Persist de-identified Session\n(Mesmerize UUID — not patient id)
API --> App : {\n  sessionId,\n  mesmerizeAccessToken,\n  …\n}

note over API, DB
  Backend may store: sessionId, clinic/device group,
  ICD-10[], engagement, billing suggestions.
  Backend must **reject** payloads containing patient identifiers.
end note

== H. Clinical workflow (uses Mesmerize token + browser FHIR context) ==

App -> API : GET /api/content/recommend?…\n(ICD-10 set + device filters)\nAuthorization: Bearer {mesmerizeAccessToken}
API --> App : Ranked education content
App -> API : Device pair + POST command\n(push to exam room via device-realtime)
note right of App
  Device path is server-mediated (ADR-007).
  Parallel ambient AI in Athena (if any)
  is independent — Mesmerize is not a scribe.
end note

== I. Optional writeback (still 3-legged EHR token, browser-side) ==

App -> App : Physician reviews billing evidence\n(human-in-the-loop; Nurse/MA cannot approve writeback)
alt Writeback enabled for customer
  App -> FHIR : **POST /DocumentReference**\nAuthorization: Bearer {EHR access_token}\n(engagement / service-delivery summary;\nLOINC 69730-0 framing per architecture)
  FHIR --> App : 201 Created
else Writeback disabled (per-org config)
  App -> App : Skip EHR write; export/audit only
end

== J. Failure / security paths (summary) ==

note over Launch, AS
  **Reject / abort if:**
  • state mismatch or missing code
  • private_key_jwt assertion invalid
  • scope escalation beyond MVP set
  • token response missing patient/encounter when launch/encounter required
  • Platform API called with EHR Bearer token
  • standalone launch attempted in MVP build
end note

legend right
  |= Concept |= Mesmerize choice |
  | Grant | authorization_code (3-legged) |
  | Launch | EHR launch only (Athena chart) |
  | SSO | Athena / EHR — no Mesmerize login |
  | Client auth | private_key_jwt |
  | Client id | mesmerize-content-evidence |
  | FHIR token | Browser only |
  | Platform auth | Separate Mesmerize session token |
  | Pilot EHR | athenahealth (Epic/Cerner later) |
endlegend

@enduml
